alerts.description: There is a high potential for the development of black ice.

There is a risk of gale-force gusts (Level 2 of 4).
Height range: > 600 m; Max. gusts: 55-70 km/h; Wind direction: south-west; Increased gusts: in exposed locations ~ 75 km/h

There is a risk of storm-force gusts (Level 2 of 4).
Height range: > 1000 m; Max. gusts: 85-100 km/h; Wind direction: south-west; Increased gusts: in exposed locations ~ 110 km/h

There is a risk of persistent rain (Level 2 of 4).
Precipitation amounts: 40-60 l/m²; in windward areas: < 80 l/m²

There is a high risk of black ice due to freezing rain and ice accretion (Level 3 of 4).
Height range: > 800 m
